@abhinav @blampe @breerly 


cc @prashantv  @Raynos

Implements the basic parts PEP440. It is not complete as it does not implement the replacements, but since those are not implemented in pip either, I don't think it is a big deal for now.

We don't use distlib's version as our version is ~50 % faster (we don't parse the string twice !). I also believe our implementation is simpler.

@jvkersch

@jonparrott Asked that I make a "do not merge" PR out of this, as a placeholder for the work remaining in #1998.

When I wrote this code (May 10th), the system tests all passed without issue (THAT WAS NOT TRUE WHEN I WROTE IT), but the unit tests are currently very broken by this change.

I am very much intentionally leaving the "Allow edits from maintainers" box checked, so anyone is free to fix the unit tests :grinning:

ScroogeGen migrated into SimpleCodegenTask;  
synthetic_target_type property deprecated, method used instead; 
dummy_generator android_generator moved to contrib/scrooge/examples

- Add blinker as an optional requirement, if not provided signals will be ignored unless there is a handler trying to connect, in that case it will raise an exception informing that blinker needs to be installed.
- Add documentation for signals module
- Add test_signals to test only that all signals are properly emitted

```python
from nailgun import entities, signals

@signals.pre_create.connect
def pre_create_handler(sender, create_missing):
    if isinstance(sender, entities.Organization):
        print("Org will be created, lets assign its domain")
        sender.domain = "http://example.com"

@signals.post_create.connect
def post_create_handler(sender, entity):
    if isinstance(entity, entities.Organization):
        print("Org {e.id} was created with domain {e.domain}!!!".format(e=entity))


>>> org = Organization(cfg, id=1).create()
>>> 'Org will be created, lets assign its domain' 
>>> 'Org 1 was created with domain http://example.com!!!'
```

We can now easily depend on anything in the Closure Library (e.g. JSPB) and it
won't add 11mB to tensorboard.html un-compiled.

@jameswex note that `goog.require('goog.object');` needed to be added to a `<script>` tag.
